    "body": "### Description\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/v2.1.0/lsp/gopls.lua#L39\n\nThis line calls `vim.notify` in callback passed to `vim.system` which causes the error\n\n```\nvim/_editor.lua:0: E5560: nvim_echo must not be called in a fast event context\n```\n\nSimply wrapping this line with `vim.schedule` fixed this.\n\n```diff\n-         vim.notify((\"[gopls] cmd failed with code %d: %s\\n%s\"):format(output.code, cmd, output.stderr))\n+        vim.schedule(function()\n+          vim.notify((\"[gopls] cmd failed with code %d: %s\\n%s\"):format(output.code, cmd, output.stderr))\n+        end)\n```\n\nBut I'm very new to neovim so not sure this is correct fix or there's more preferrable manner.",
